Added features:
- Alpha patch                   float alpha in config.h to determine transparency
- Scrollback patch              
    - Shift + Mouse wheel       goes through terminal history
    - Ctrl  + Shift + j/k       goes through terminal history
- Anysize patch                 terminal windows fill entire given space


For alpha patch to work the xcompmgr or sth similar needs to be running in the background.


Original README:


st - simple terminal
--------------------
st is a simple terminal emulator for X which sucks less.


Requirements
------------
In order to build st you need the Xlib header files.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (st is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install st (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running st
----------
If you did not install st with make clean install, you must compile
the st terminfo entry with the following command:

    tic -sx st.info

See the man page for additional details.

